grid.text: 9. Grabs his forelock, raises on his knee
9. Sits back on his knee, looks down.
9. Raises on his knee and looks up.
9. Sits back, raises again and slides to face front. Looks down and slashes his fan to the right.
4. Raises his fan and lashes it left and right.
4. L. soft stamp, R. stamp & Open fan. R, Circle to 8.
9. Open-retreat, Go to 3 with L-R-L Head-motion.
3. Take the corner, Point and look at the right

captions.translation: And so, it was in the early days of our history,
captions.transcription: Mata waga chō no sono hajime

captions.translation: the Twelfth of the Imperial LIne, the Emperor Keiko,
had a son known by the name
captions.transcription: miko no mikato no on-na ō ba

captions.translation: Yamato-dake.
The wild barbarians! he received the order to subdue them.
captions.transcription: Kiui ō Taiji no chiku ō uke.

captions.translation: The barrier check points far behind as yet further to the East.
The road of his journey to the Eastern provinces took him.
captions.transcription: Azuma no tabi no michi sugara

captions.translation: Even at Ise and Owari the waves on the sea rise and return!
captions.transcription: Ise ya Owari no umizura ni tatsu nami made mo

captions.translation: With envy he wondered always,
when he too might find himslef, with foam-drenched sleeves
captions.transcription: itsu ka warera mo kaeru nami no

captions.translation: returning home, even as he continued on his way.
captions.transcription: koromode ni arama shi to amoi-tsuzukete-yuku hodo ni.

captions.translation: In the battles in one place and in the next
captions.transcription: Koko ya kashiko no tatakai ni

captions.translation: Men and horses: their bodies crushed in their caverns,
captions.transcription: Jin-ba gankutsu ni mi ō kudaki

captions.translation: their blood on the battlefields a river,
captions.transcription: Chi wa takuroku no kawa to natte

captions.translation: their shields swept away on crimson waves again and again.
captions.transcription: kōha tate nagashi sudo ni oyoberu ebisu mo

captions.translation: Finally the barbarians removed their helmets,
captions.transcription: kabuto ō nuide hoko ō fuse

captions.translation: lay down their arms and were made to surrender.
From the time of this Prince's reign, the royal sport of hunting was begun.
captions.transcription: Mi-koto no gyō yori mi-kariba ō susume tamaeri.

captions.translation: It was an incident that occured,
on the twentieth day of the tenth month:
captions.transcription: hatsu ka amari no koto nareba.

captions.translation: Everywhere the autumn tints had faded,
captions.transcription: yo-mo no momiji mo fuyugare no

captions.translation: and even on the distant winter withered mountiains,
the traces of the first snow fall could be seen.
The barbarians surrounding him on every side
Set fire to the grass of the withered fields, and as the blaze burned high
captions.transcription: Kare-no no kusa ni hi ō kake

captions.translation: and as the blaze burned high with heavy lingering billows of smoke.
Began to beat their war drums in the signal to attack.
The Towering flames! as the attack blazed forward
The Prince drew his sword
The Prince drewing his sword,
wielded it about him.
At once, the flames drew back,
as it mowed down the grasses in all directions.
The spirit of the sword became a strom
captions.transcription: tsurugi no seirei arashi to natte

captions.translation: blasting back the raging flames and grasses too.
The blaze lit up the heavens, covered the earth!
captions.transcription: ten ni kakayaki chi ni michite

captions.translation: A furnace of fierced flames turned back to devour the ennemy forces.
captions.transcription: myō-ka wa kaette kataki ō yakeba

captions.translation: Thus the countless barbarians
captions.transcription: su man gi no Yebisu-domo wa

captions.translation: and cavalrymen were brought down.
So in later years the Empire was at peace:
So much so that the people forgot to bar the doors of their houses.
This is because of the 'Grass-cutter', it was said.
captions.transcription: sono Kusanagi no yue to ka ya.

captions.translation: An now, this auspicious omened blade
that you must forge!
Is there any reason it shold be a lesser blade than that ?
captions.transcription: ika de sore ni wa otorubeki

captions.translation: Munechika, keir of the jhouse of proud tradition,
set your heart at rest and go home now.
captions.transcription: kokoro yasuku mo omoite ge-kō shi tamae.
